        <entry>
            <title>Hello from Org!</title>
            <link href="https://blog.bastidehub.xyz/posts/hello-org-post/" />
            <updated>2026-03-27T00:00:00Z</updated>
            <id>https://blog.bastidehub.xyz/posts/hello-org-post/</id>
            <author>
                <name>Xavier Brinon</name>
            </author>
            <content type="html">
                &lt;p&gt;This is the first blog post written in org-mode and converted to Markdown by the pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Why org-mode?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Org-mode is a powerful authoring format native to Emacs. It supports:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structured headings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rich metadata via keywords and property drawers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source code blocks with syntax highlighting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Links and images&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Next steps&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pipeline converts this &lt;code&gt;.org&lt;/code&gt; file into &lt;code&gt;.md&lt;/code&gt; with YAML frontmatter, then Eleventy builds it into HTML.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
        </entry>
